</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#AADDDD><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unakilosgaremonde.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nakilos Garemonde</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>10/5/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>2:08:47 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Stormtower, FGs can be done with a single group...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">ya i did FG's, single group, with only the warrior being 55 +<br>
<br>
so i guess ya can't put em on the calendar...hehe</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#DDDDAA><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaddiefaye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maddie Faye</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>10/5/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>2:34:07 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Stormtower, FGs can be done with a single group...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;FGs were my first big raid experience. I'm sure a lot of people had the same experience, because you can join FG raids several levels before you can enter the planes or go on a dragon raid.&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
Just because they were your first big raid experience, does not entitle them to remain on the calendar.  There was a time on this server that the Froglock King in Lower Guk was considered a raid.<br>
<br>
The reasoning that because the respawn time is so long, is why it's on the calendar, is out right rediculous.  If we operate under that logic then we might as well add the Ishva spawn to the calendar; along with the multitude of epic quests spawns that are out there.<br>
<br>
The time for FG on the raid calendar has passed.  FG's are not even a good introduction to large scale raids anymore as Kunark dungeons have a rapid respawn rate and don't allow you to take your sweet time with a raid.<br>
<br>
You can do FG, as pointed out, by a small group of people.  The whole reason for the calendar from the beginning was to help in the management of events that required large groups of people to participate.<br>
<br>
Since you can easily do this with 6 of the right people, or no doubt with a group of 12 50+; I think this needs to be pulled from the calendar.<br>
<br>
BTW, lower level people could do a lot more if they just TRIED.  12-20 40-45s can accomplish quite a bit as working as one; however they choose not to.<br>
<br>
In review of the calendar it seems FGs are scheduled on rare occasions anyway; I see no valid reason to really respect these raids going forward; not to mention the recent problems with Nagy groups taking down FGs in order to get to the dragon (understandable).<br>
<br>
I'm starting to think that the calendar is benefiting more the casual players, than the serious players.  I'll post more later as to why I feel this way, but many others before me have pointed this out; and I'm finally starting to understand why.<br>
<br>
Maddie<br>
