<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#DDDDAA><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustormtower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormtower</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>10/5/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>4:47:09 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://members.hometown.aol.com/_ht_a/twormtwower/myhomepage/st60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Stormtower, FGs can be done with a single group...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">*sobers up*<br>
<br>
I think the point that no one has mentioned is:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The Fire Giant raids are stopping the Nagafen raiders from going forward.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
There are a lot of people who want to kill the dragons as soon as they spawn.  A fire giant raid in progress slows down the process.<br>
<br>
Lets take a situation:<br>
<br>
Assume that the dragon raiders are full of newbies.  It stands to reason that they would take a lot longer to kill the dragon than the &quot;professional&quot; EQ Player.<br>
<br>
Assume also that the fire giant raiders are full of newbies.  Assuming that these raiders are using the FGs to learn the basics of raiding, they are not as efficient as your &quot;professional&quot; EQ Player.<br>
<br>
Assume that the &quot;professional&quot; EQ Player is playing a slightly lower level character in order to obtain one of the epic quest items from the dragons.  As far as this player is concerned, the faster the dragon raid goes, the more likely he'll get to kill the dragons and get the item.<br>
<br>
The dragon raiders are balked by the fire giant raiders -- they don't want to interrupt, and they would rather save their efforts for the big push.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile, the &quot;professional&quot; EQ Player is getting frustrated waiting for the dragon raid to start, knowing that he could be playing his primary somewhere else.  Ideas of bringing his primary in and killing the Fire Giants himself so that the Naggy raid can start are foremost in his imagination.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Now ... what's my opinion on the subject?<br>
<br>
Fire Giants are a raid unto themselves.  There were no arguments against it during Arideth's meeting; the arguments were over the Efreeti.<br>
<br>
Sure you can do FG's with one group.  Is it worth it to that one group?  Probably not.  Why would they do it?  To open up the path to the dragon.<br>
<br>
The only other reason I can think of is to farm the items.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Why is the Ishva Mal not a raid?  It's a 36 hour spawn, and it's just slightly less difficult than the FGs, depending on who goes on the raid?<br>
<br>
My opinion: the situation may have changed now that the Ishva is dropping epic quest items (unconfirmed, just going by what I read above).  The demand for Ishva was not that high before.  The primary reason to camp it in the past was for the Summon Corpse spell.<br>
<br>
Besides, a group or two of level 30's can kill Ishva Mal.<br>
<br>
<br>
*goes back to the case of vodka*</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR></TABLE><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=95%><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980general.showMessage?topicID=4640.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980general.showMessage?topicID=4655.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95% BORDER=0><TR><TD><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4551.topic&index=11><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980general.emailToFriend?topicID=4551.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/images/email.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Email This To a Friend"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;Email This To a Friend</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980general.threadControl?topicID=4551.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Topic Control Image"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;Topic Commands (Moderator only)</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980general.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4551.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Subscribe</FONT></A>  <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Click to receive email notification of replies</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980general.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4551.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Unsubscribe</FONT></A>  <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</FONT><BR></TD><TD></TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN=3 ALIGN=CENTER><BR><FORM ACTION=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum METHOD=POST><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Jump to: </FONT><SELECT NAME=forumName><OPTION VALUE=prexus95980general>General<OPTION VALUE=prexus9598